<p>Barcelona, the colourful capital of Catalonia, is a popular destination for tourists and wanderers, usually making the top spot in many people's Spain travel bucket lists.</p>
<p>In fact, according to a 2023 report by the Barcelona Tourism Board, visitors to Barcelona is increasing year-on-year by 12.4% with Barcelona Airport handling over 3.3 million passengers.</p>
<p>That being said, what should you know about <a href="https://spainguides.com/spain-travel/things-to-do-in-barcelona/">coming to Barcelona</a> for the first time in order to make your visit truly special and perhaps even worthy of a return trip?</p>
<p>Fortunately, this article answers that question, serving as your complete guide to visiting Barcelona.</p>
