	<h4>Accommodation</h4>
<p>When it comes to accommodation, there is no shortage of choices in Barcelona as there are many options which are available for all kinds of travellers.</p>
<p>The Gothic Quarter is perfect for history lovers and those who want to be in the heart of the city's medieval streets, while El Born offers a vibrant mix of boutique hotels, trendy bars, and close proximity to major attractions.</p>
<p>If you're looking for a more modern atmosphere, <a href="https://spainguides.com/beach-hotels-in-spain/">Eixample is filled with elegant hotels</a> and upscale shopping, and its grid-like streets are home to some of the city’s best dining experiences.</p>
<p>For a quieter, more residential feel, Gracia provides a village-like atmosphere with cosy guesthouses and local restaurants. Beach lovers will enjoy Barceloneta, which boasts accommodation near the sea with stunning views.</p>
<p>If your looking to enjoy the city’s nightlife, Poble Sec and El Raval offer lively, hipster accommodations close to clubs and bars.</p>
