	<figure id="attachment_10602" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-10602" style="width: 830px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-10602" src="https://spainguides.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Madrid-Plaza-Espana.jpg" alt="Plaza Espana" width="830" height="530" srcset="https://spainguides.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Madrid-Plaza-Espana.jpg 830w, https://spainguides.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Madrid-Plaza-Espana-300x192.jpg 300w, https://spainguides.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/Madrid-Plaza-Espana-768x490.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 830px) 100vw, 830px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-10602" class="wp-caption-text">Plaza Espana - Madrid</figcaption></figure>
<p>Spain isn’t just about beaches and sangria (although we’re not complaining about those either). Its cities are a vibrant tapestry of history, culture, and modern-day cool. From the <a href="https://spainguides.com/spain-travel/best-coffee-shops-in-barcelona/">bustling energy of Barcelona</a> to the soulful <a href="https://spainguides.com/top-destinations/seville-spain/">charm of Seville</a>, Spain’s urban scene is a must-experience.</p>
<p>Let’s start with the big hitters: Barcelona, with its iconic architecture, world-class art scene, and electric nightlife, is a magnet for culture vultures and party animals alike. <a href="https://spainguides.com/spain-travel/what-to-see-in-madrid/">Madrid, Spain’s capital</a>, is a city that never sleeps, offering a mix of history, culture, and non-stop entertainment.</p>
<p>But Spain’s urban magic isn’t confined to these two giants. Valencia, with its futuristic <a href="https://spainguides.com/city-of-arts-science-valencia/">City of Arts and Sciences</a> and delicious paella, offers a unique blend of old and new. <a href="https://spainguides.com/gastronomy-of-spain/san-sebastian/">San Sebastian</a>, a foodie’s paradise, boasts stunning beaches and a laid-back vibe. And Seville, with its Moorish architecture and passionate flamenco, will transport you to another world.</p>
<p>For a taste of history, <a href="https://spainguides.com/mezquita-mosque-cathedral-cordoba/">head to Cordoba</a>, where the Mezquita is a breathtaking testament to Islamic Spain. And don’t forget Bilbao, transformed by the Guggenheim Museum into a global art destination.</p>
<p>Beyond the big-name attractions, Spain’s cities offer countless hidden gems. Wander through charming neighbourhoods, discover local markets, and soak up the atmosphere in the <a href="https://spainguides.com/spanish-tapas-everything-you-need-to-know-more/">incredible tapas scene</a>. Spain’s urban scene is a melting pot of cultures, where tradition meets modernity.</p>
<p>Get ready to explore the great Urban Travel getaways in Spain, and fall in love with the beating heart of this incredible country.</p>
