	<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter wp-image-1119 size-full" src="https://spainguides.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Benidorm-Beach.jpg" alt="Benidorm Spain" width="830" height="530" srcset="https://spainguides.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Benidorm-Beach.jpg 830w, https://spainguides.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Benidorm-Beach-300x192.jpg 300w, https://spainguides.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Benidorm-Beach-768x490.jpg 768w, https://spainguides.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Benidorm-Beach-600x383.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 830px) 100vw, 830px" /></p>
<p>Benidorm, often referred to as the "Manhattan of the Mediterranean," is one of Spain's most popular tourist destinations.</p>
<p>Known for its stunning beaches, lively nightlife, and year-round sunshine, <a href="https://spainguides.com/spain-travel/best-things-to-do-in-benidorm/">Benidorm offers a wide range of experiences</a> for all types of visitors.</p>
<p>With so many excellent <a href="https://destinia.com/en/hotels/europe/spain/alicante/benidorm/ht-32776" target="_blank" rel="noopener">hotels in Benidorm</a> to choose from, this guide will help you find the best area or neighbourhood, whether you are looking for a lively atmosphere, cultural immersion, or a quiet seaside retreat.</p>
<h4>Looking to Book a Hotel?</h4>
