	<h3>Benidorm Old Town</h3>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-18223" src="https://spainguides.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Old-Town-Benidorm.jpg" alt="Old Town Benidorm" width="830" height="530" srcset="https://spainguides.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Old-Town-Benidorm.jpg 830w, https://spainguides.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Old-Town-Benidorm-300x192.jpg 300w, https://spainguides.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Old-Town-Benidorm-768x490.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 830px) 100vw, 830px" /></p>
<p>Benidorm's Old Town is a charming district filled with history and character. Unlike the high-rise buildings that dominate much of the city, the Old Town is a maze of narrow, cobbled streets lined with whitewashed houses, traditional shops, and cosy tapas bars. The atmosphere here is more relaxed and offers a taste of authentic Spanish life.</p>
<p><strong>Who It’s Ideal For:</strong> This area is perfect for those interested in exploring the cultural and historical aspects of Benidorm. If you enjoy strolling through picturesque streets, visiting local markets, and dining at authentic Spanish restaurants, the Old Town will be an ideal base for your stay.</p>
<h4>Points of Interest:</h4>
<p><strong>Balcón del Mediterráneo:</strong> Also known as the <a href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/usRqPFdoudtM4nb9A" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Castle Viewpoint,</a> this iconic spot offers breathtaking panoramic views of the Mediterranean Sea. It's a great place for a leisurely walk and taking memorable photos.</p>
<p><strong>Iglesia de San Jaime y Santa Ana:</strong> This beautiful 18th-century church, located at the top of the Old Town, is one of Benidorm’s most important landmarks. The church’s blue-domed roof is a striking feature of the town’s skyline.</p>
<p><strong>Tapas Bars:</strong> The Old Town is famous for its numerous tapas bars, where you can enjoy a variety of <a href="https://spainguides.com/spanish-cuisine/">traditional Spanish dishes</a> in a lively atmosphere. A must-visit is "Tapas Alley" (Calle Santo Domingo), where you can sample some of the best tapas in the region.</p>
<h3>Levante Beach Area</h3>
<figure id="attachment_1119" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-1119" style="width: 830px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-1119" src="https://spainguides.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Benidorm-Beach.jpg" alt="Benidorm Beach" width="830" height="530" srcset="https://spainguides.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Benidorm-Beach.jpg 830w, https://spainguides.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Benidorm-Beach-300x192.jpg 300w, https://spainguides.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Benidorm-Beach-768x490.jpg 768w, https://spainguides.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Benidorm-Beach-600x383.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 830px) 100vw, 830px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-1119" class="wp-caption-text">Benidorm Beach</figcaption></figure>
<p>The Levante Beach area is the heart of Benidorm’s tourist scene and is particularly popular with visitors. The area is known for its vibrant atmosphere, with a long stretch of sandy beach lined with bars, restaurants, and shops. This is where you’ll find the majority of Benidorm’s nightlife, making it a lively spot both day and night.</p>
<p><strong>Who It’s Ideal For:</strong> This area is ideal for those who want to be in the centre of the action. If you enjoy spending your days on the beach and your nights exploring a wide range of bars, clubs, and entertainment venues, Levante Beach is the place for you.</p>
<h4>Points of Interest:</h4>
<p><strong>Levante Beach:</strong> One of the <a href="https://spainguides.com/visit-spain/best-beaches-spain/">most famous beaches in Spain</a>, Levante Beach offers golden sands, clear waters, and a lively promenade. It’s the perfect spot for sunbathing, water sports, or simply relaxing with a cocktail at one of the beachside bars.</p>
<p><strong>Nightlife Area</strong>: The epicentre of <a href="https://summertakeover.com/resort/benidorm/nightlife/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Benidorm’s nightlife</a>, packed with bars, clubs, and live entertainment venues. It’s a great place for those looking to enjoy a fun night out.</p>
<p><strong>Benidorm Palace:</strong> This iconic venue offers spectacular dinner shows featuring live music, dance, and cabaret performances. It’s a great place for an evening of entertainment.</p>
<h3>Rincón de Loix</h3>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-27193" src="https://spainguides.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Rincon-de-Loix.jpg" alt="Rincon de Loix Benidorm" width="830" height="530" srcset="https://spainguides.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Rincon-de-Loix.jpg 830w, https://spainguides.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Rincon-de-Loix-300x192.jpg 300w, https://spainguides.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Rincon-de-Loix-768x490.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 830px) 100vw, 830px" /></p>
<p>Located at the far end of Levante Beach, Rincin de Loix is a modern, cosmopolitan neighbourhood that has become a favourite among families and expats. The area is well-equipped with supermarkets, pubs, and a wide range of accommodation options, making it a convenient and comfortable place to stay.</p>
<p><strong>Who It’s Ideal For:</strong> Rincon de Loix is ideal for families and groups looking for a comfortable stay with easy access to amenities and activities. It’s also popular with those who prefer a home-away-from-home feel.</p>
<h4>Points of Interest:</h4>
<p><strong>Aqualandia:</strong> One of Europe’s largest water parks, <a href="https://spainguides.com/spain-travel/best-water-parks-in-spain/">Aqualandia is a must-visit for families with children</a>. The park offers a variety of water slides, wave pools, and attractions suitable for all ages.</p>
<p><strong>Mundomar:</strong> A marine and animal park located near Aqualandia, Mundomar is perfect for a family day out. The park features dolphin and sea lion shows, as well as opportunities to interact with various animals.</p>
<p><strong>Rincón de Loix Market:</strong> A popular shopping destination, the market offers a variety of stalls selling everything from souvenirs to food products. It’s a great place to find familiar items during your holiday.</p>
<h3>Poniente Beach Area</h3>
<figure id="attachment_3047" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3047" style="width: 830px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3047" src="https://spainguides.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Benidorm_Beach.jpg" alt="Benidorm Poniente Beach" width="830" height="530" srcset="https://spainguides.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Benidorm_Beach.jpg 830w, https://spainguides.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Benidorm_Beach-300x192.jpg 300w, https://spainguides.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Benidorm_Beach-768x490.jpg 768w, https://spainguides.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Benidorm_Beach-600x383.jpg 600w, https://spainguides.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Benidorm_Beach-470x300.jpg 470w" sizes="(max-width: 830px) 100vw, 830px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3047" class="wp-caption-text">Benidorm Poniente Beach</figcaption></figure>
<p>Poniente Beach is the quieter, more relaxed counterpart to Levante Beach. This area has undergone significant development in recent years, with a new promenade and several luxury apartment buildings. The atmosphere here is more laid-back, making it a great choice for those looking to escape the hustle and bustle of central Benidorm.</p>
<p><strong>Who It’s Ideal For:</strong> Poniente Beach is perfect for those seeking a peaceful stay, away from the crowds. It’s an ideal spot for families, couples, and older visitors who prefer a more tranquil environment.</p>
<h4>Points of Interest:</h4>
<p><strong>Poniente Beach:</strong> Known for its clean, golden sands and calm waters, Poniente Beach is a great spot for swimming, sunbathing, and enjoying a quiet day by the sea.</p>
<p>Parque de Elche: Located at the end of Poniente Beach, this park is a lovely place for a stroll or a picnic. It’s also known as "Dove Park" due to the many pigeons that frequent the area.</p>
<p><strong>Benidorm Island:</strong> Just off the coast of Poniente Beach, Benidorm Island is a popular spot for boat trips and snorkelling. The island offers clear waters and abundant marine life, making it a great destination for nature lovers.</p>
<h3>Sierra Helada &amp; Albir</h3>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-27189" src="https://spainguides.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Sierra-Helada-Benidorm.jpg" alt="Sierra Helada Benidorm" width="830" height="530" srcset="https://spainguides.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Sierra-Helada-Benidorm.jpg 830w, https://spainguides.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Sierra-Helada-Benidorm-300x192.jpg 300w, https://spainguides.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Sierra-Helada-Benidorm-768x490.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 830px) 100vw, 830px" /></p>
<p>For those who enjoy outdoor activities and breathtaking natural scenery, the <a href="https://en.visitbenidorm.es/ver/3863/sierra-helada-natural-park-benidorm.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Sierra Helada Natural Park</a> and the nearby Albir area offer a different side of Benidorm. This area is known for its rugged coastline, hiking trails, and stunning views of the Mediterranean.</p>
<p><strong>Who It’s Ideal For:</strong> Sierra Helada and Albir are perfect for nature lovers and those who prefer to be slightly removed from the busy city centre. It’s an excellent choice for those looking to explore the great outdoors and enjoy a quieter, more serene setting.</p>
<h4>Points of Interest:</h4>
<p><strong>Sierra Helada Natural Park</strong>: This protected area offers some of the best hiking trails in the region, with paths that wind through the mountains and offer spectacular views of the coast. The park is also home to various plant and animal species, making it a great spot for nature enthusiasts.</p>
<p><strong>Albir Beach</strong>: Just a short drive from Benidorm, Albir Beach is a quieter alternative to the busier beaches in Benidorm. The beach has a relaxed atmosphere and is popular with those seeking a more tranquil beach experience.</p>
<p><strong>Lighthouse Walk</strong>: The walk to the Albir lighthouse is a popular activity for visitors to the area. The path is well-paved and offers stunning coastal views, making it a perfect spot for a scenic stroll.</p>
